Well, Mr. Perfectionist… I found the perfect country after having lived in four cities and15 countries for 36 years. I have reached the conclusion. I am happy in this country where not everything is perfect, but people work around it and what matters is that unlike the old-fashioned thinking, it supports other countries.

When I was a little girl, my friend’s dad who had a British passport used to say to me whenever I visited, “America is the greatest nation in the world and you should migrate there when you grow up.” He didn’t say it to taunt me, but he was an enormous patriot because his parents migrated to the United Kingdom for a better life.

I am not against moving to another country when thrust upon you for whatever reason, but going to another country is not a game. You conquer it and it conquers you. You enter the country of strangers, feel the pains, smells and taste the variances and then embrace all of what is new.

Pick up things that make life better. And UNITE together as a single unit of MULTIPUL nations, all religions and culture just the way your ancestors did when you figured out how to make fire so that it could be spread to fuel of your choice.
